hondo717: The comment/question is a good one. Most really top notch players think IMPs is a better form of scoring, as there is less luck involved. However, I personally prefer match points, as I think it is a much more interesting game. In MP on every hand, you are trying to maximize the number of tricks you take. In IMPs, for example, once they are in game, doesn't matter if they make 4 or 5. Conversely, in match points, if you are defending and take one more trick than the other pairs, even if they still make their contract, you will do very well. That is why I like match points, because every hand you have to concentrate. |
